    110. Here, we adopt a variant of the model that interpolates the path from points A to H of the original model by Purvis et al. (Ref. 104 ). Moreover, we use a Be(10 s 3 p /3 s 2 p ), H(4 s /2 s ) basis set (included in the Supplementary Material) which differs slightly from the original double-ζ basis set used in previous studies. In our basis set the tight beryllium p primitive function was decontracted to better describe core correlation of the Be atom. Google Scholar
